    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm just saying it feels like those \"mitigation strategies\" often fail in practice and end up being just buzzwords for developers to build luxury condos. it seems like the real-world result is always more displacement and less actual affordability. isn't it more realistic to say that high-density zoning is fundamentally a tool for gentrification?",
